quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  27,83,"Upon the day when We shall muster out of every nation a troop of those that cried lies to Our signs, duly disposed"
  27,84,"till, when they are come, He shall say, 'Did you cry lies to My signs, not comprehending them in knowledge, or what have you been doing"
  27,85,"And the Word shall fall upon them because of the evil they committed, while they speak naught"
  27,86,"Have they not seen how We made the night for them, to repose in it, and the day, to see? Surely in that is a sign for a people who are believers"
  27,87,"On the day the Trumpet is blown, and terrified is whosoever is in the heavens and earth, excepting whom God wills, and every one shall come to Him, all utterly abject"
  27,88,"and thou shalt see the mountains, that thou supposest fixed, passing by like clouds -- God's handiwork, who has created everything very well. He is aware of the things you do"
  27,89,"Whosoever comes with a good deed, he shall have better than it; and they shall be secure from terror that day"
  27,90,"And whosoever comes with an evil deed, their faces shall be thrust into the Fire: 'Are you recompensed but for what you did"
  27,91,I have only been commanded to serve the Lord of this territory which He has made sacred; to Him belongs everything. And I have been commanded to be of those that surrender
  27,92,"and to recite the Koran. So whosoever is guided, is only guided to his own gain; and whosoever goes astray, say: 'I am naught but a warner"
  27,93,"And say: 'Praise belongs to God. He shall show you His signs and you will recognise them. Thy Lord is not heedless of the things you do"